{
  "texts": [
    "In a survey on bias and fairness [96], fairness is defined as the lack of bias and discrimination.",
    "Different biases can affect the model's inner decision-making process when dealing with AI systems, hampering fairness.",
    "AI bias can be classified into three groups, depending on where it has the most effect: data to algorithm, algorithm to user, and user to data [96].",
    "Bias from data to algorithm only derives from the dataset itself.",
    "Examples of such bias are measurement bias (which arises from how a particular feature is measured), sampling bias (which arises from how data is sampled, especially in underrepresented classes), and representation bias (which arises from how a feature is represented)."
  ]
}